channel.title: Clean up :: AWS Intership Report
channel.description: Congratulations on completing this workshop! In this workshop, you learned architecture patterns for accessing Amazon S3 without using the Public Internet. By creating a gateway endpoint, you enabled direct communication between EC2 resources and Amazon S3, without traversing an Internet Gateway. By creating an interface endpoint you extended S3 connectivity to resources running in your on-premises data center via AWS Site-to-Site VPN or Direct Connect. clean up Navigate to Hosted Zones on the left side of Route 53 console. Click the name of s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com zone. Click Delete and confirm deletion by typing delete.
